{
  "text": "The results also showed that fertilization rate was 60.05% (276/456) in breeding season, while it was 53.9% (145/269) in non-breeding season. Similar observation has been reported by Camarago et al. [CITATION_1] and Kharchi et al. [CITATION_2] . These results might be attributed to the effect of heat stress on oocyte quality could lead to seasonal variation in the success rate of.",
  "correct_citation": {
